<p><strong>3D Beer Pong - Marist College Style </strong> <br />
</p>
<p>3D Beer Pong<br />
</p>
<p>Rules and Regulations: Version 1: Center</p>
<p>
  1. 5 layers = 25-16-9-4-1 = 55 <br />
  2. Stand 4 feet back from the table <br />
  3. The plane of the table may not be broken breaking of plane results in forfeiture of turn <br />
  4. Teams of four (4) <br />
  5. When cup is hit, drinking must go from top to bottom <br />
  6. Hitting top cup results in five (5) cups for opposing team hitting second row results in 4 cups bottom layer results in one (1) cup for opposing team <br />
  7. To achieve victory one team must reach the point of no return that is to have more cups hit than the opposing team can match <br />
  8. When the point of no return is reached, the losing team must drink the remaining cups <br />
</p>
<p>Version 2: Traditional<br />
  <br />
  1. 2 sets of 3 layers = 9-4-1 = 13       </p>
<p>2. Teams of two (2)<br />
  3. When cup is hit, drinking must go from top to bottom<br />
  4. Hitting top cup results in three (3) cups for opposing team hitting second row results in two (2) cups, bottom layer results in one (1) cup for opposing team<br />
  5. To achieve victory one team must clear opponents  cups, as in traditional beer pong<br />
  6. Losing team must drink remaining cups of winning team</p>
<p>Source: Beer Pong. (n.d.). <em>Beer Pong Rule Collection</em>. Retrieved October 29, 2012, from http://www.circlesbarngrill.com/Beer%20Pong.html</p>
